article.description: — Mason Archambault's 19 points helped South Dakota defeat Long Island University 68-58 on Tuesday.
article.headline: South Dakota secures 68-58 victory against LIU
article.linkText: South Dakota secures 68-58 victory against LIU
article.story: CYPRESS LAKE, Fla. -- — Mason Archambault's 19 points helped South Dakota defeat Long Island University 68-58 on Tuesday. Archambault also contributed four steals for the Coyotes (3-2). Tasos Kamateros scored 13 points and added six rebounds. Paul Bruns recorded 11 points and was 4 of 10 shooting (1 for 5 from distance). Marko Maletic led the way for the Sharks (1-3) with 19 points. LIU also got 12 points and two steals from R.J. Greene. In addition, Cheikh Ndiaye finished with six points and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
